title: White Noise
description:
When Xavier de Le Rue, considered by most of his peers, as the best big mountain rider out there, has a killer season and reveals his personal approach to snowboarding, you get White NOISE, TimeLine Films second Movie after last year success This Is My Winter.
White Noise will bring you from aggressive spine, and bergshrund riding in Haines, Alaska called the Image factory. Xavier still with Victor his younger brother will then discover a new kind of spot, and they will ride underground inside dream like cave in south of france. Last but not least, Xavier will push riding boundaries along with freeskieur Samuel Anthamatten in the Zermatt alps. Never two freeriders, snowboard and ski did such productive sessions just a Blink away from Infamous Matterhorn.

Awards:

Xavier received award for "best guts" at the The Reels, the international snowboard film festival in Annecy.
White Noise received best cinematography and public special award at saint Lary International freeride film festival


White Noise features Xavier de Le Rue ( FRA), Victor de Le Rue (FRA), Samuel Anthamatten (SWI)

filmed in:
Haines, Alaska (USA)
Devoluy, Haute Alpes (FRA)
Marécottes, Valais (SWI)
Engelberg, Obwald (SWI)
Zermatt, Valais (SWI)

www.timelinemissions.com
